10.17.24  12:27 pm   Why is EADGBE standard guitar tuning 

      maybe it's a compromise between what works good for melodies and what works good for chords. what would work great for melodies is if all the intervals were the same (EADGCF), but then you'd probably never be able to play any open chords that way, so it appears that the pattern gets a little nudge to bring the highest 2 strings back into the same harmonic neighborhood as the rest

10.15.24  11:11 pm   right now i think you're doing a system where you work on multiple videos at once thru doing one department on all the videos in a row. when you finish this current batch, will you start a new set of videos with this same approach, or do you want to go back to 1 video at a time? thank you. i'm more excited for your content than ever

      in a way, this process has changed my life, the important lesson being: never do this again. On the other hand, so many aspects of this method have been so wonderful that i'd love to do it again, for an even bigger batch. but it's also likely that i will transition into content where the production time is barely any longer than the run time, or maybe equal. and so this current process may be something that pushes me to do that sooner. but, either way, it's my eagerness to get to future projects that is driving me to continue forward in this
